Package event

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • event.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Event>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Panel, Party, Talk
    public abstract class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Event>, java.io.Serializable
    This class represents an Event object. An Event can have a name, speaker, time, duration(in hours), room, capacity, and set of attendees attending. The event also contains how many computers, chairs, tables, and whether or not a projector is required for the event to run.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the event
        time - The event time
        duration - The event duration(in hours).
        roomNumber - The event room number
        capacity - This refers to the capacity of the event.
        requiredComputers - Refers to the amount of computers required for the event.
        requiredProjector - Refers to whether or not a projector is required for the event.
        requiredChairs - Refers to number of chairs required for the event.
        requiredTables - Refers to the number of tables required for the event.
        creators - Refers to the list of usernames of users that created the event.
        vipEvent - Refers to whether or not this event is limited to VIP's only
        tag - Refers to the category this event is in.
